.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-AGAIN 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-again \- revisit skipped hunks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch again
[\fB\-\-auto\-advance\fR|\fB\-\-no\-auto\-advance\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B again
clears the skipped-hunk blocklist and starts another pass through all hunks
that remain in the working tree.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-auto\-advance
Set the session default so later action commands select the next hunk when
they finish.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-auto\-advance
Set the session default so later action commands leave no hunk selected when
they finish unless they opt back in.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-skip (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-start (1)
